wie dem kritischen.  aWhat development did anti-Semitism take in Spain when, after the Banishment Edict (1492), the country was no longer a locus of co-existence for different ethnic groups? This was the topic central to the colloquium in Konstanz (May 2000), the results of which are presented here. The colloquium united anthropologists, historians and literary scholars. This interdisciplinary approach focused on the factors, spaces, figures and voices involved in anti-Jewish (and hence anti-Semitic) discourse, both in their historical context and in their literary representation. On the latter issue, as much attention is given to the apologetic as to the critical aspect.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aAntisemitismus. 4aSpanien. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAlbert, Mechthild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmrán, Rica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmselem-Szende, Line, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAponte, Yolanda Montalvo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBachoud, Andrée, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerdah, Jean-François, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBriesemeister, Dietrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrotons, María Jesús Beltrán, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCardaillac-Hermosilla, Yvette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChillida, Gonzalo Álvarez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aContreras Contreras, Jaime